{"id": "27821", "post": "<div class=\"post-27821 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-editorial tag-akamai-dns-failure tag-akamai-outage tag-cdn tag-cloud tag-offline tag-outage\" id=\"post-27821\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/outage-at-akamai-takes-down-major-internet-sites/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Outage at Akamai Takes Down Major Internet Sites</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/akamai-dns-failure/\" rel=\"tag\">akamai dns failure</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/akamai-outage/\" rel=\"tag\">akamai outage</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/cdn/\" rel=\"tag\">cdn</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/cloud/\" rel=\"tag\">cloud</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/offline/\" rel=\"tag\">offline</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/outage/\" rel=\"tag\">outage</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> July 22, 2021 @ 6:19 pm, by Jon Biloh</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/site-down-2.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-27789 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/site-down-2.jpg\" alt=\"Akamai Outage Takes Internet Down\" width=\"300\" height=\"205\" align=\"right\" hspace=\"20\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></p><p>Akamai, a leading global content delivery network, was responsible for an outage today which impacted large portions of the Internet, including popular websites FedEx, UPS, Home Depot, and many others. The outage lasted at least an hour and was the result of a \u201csoftware configuration\u201d update which went wrong, apparently causing a disruption to the DNS system at the company.</p><p>According to Akamai:</p><p><em>\u201cAt 15:46 UTC today, a software configuration update triggered a bug in the DNS system, the system that directs browsers to websites. This caused a disruption impacting availability of some customer websites. T</em><em>he disruption lasted up to an hour. Upon rolling back the software configuration update, the services resumed normal operations. Akamai can confirm this was not a cyberattack against Akamai\u2019s platform.\u201d</em></p><p>Akamai went on further in their post-outage announcement, explaining that they intend to do better in the future:</p><p>\u201cWe apologize for the inconvenience that resulted. We are reviewing our software update process to prevent future disruptions.\u201d</p><p>This is just one of many serious recent outages caused by major content delivery networks and cloud hosting providers over the past year, including CloudFlare, Microsoft Azure, Amazon AWS, IBM Cloud, and Google Cloud. The recent run of outages may cause some CIOs and CTOs to re-evaluate their reliance on centralized CND and Cloud solutions.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.lowendtalk.com/discussion/172797/akamai-outage\">Join the conversation</a> at our message board companion website, <a href=\"https://www.lowendtalk.com/discussion/172797/akamai-outage\">LowEndTalk</a>, about this latest outage.</p><p>See a larger list of impacted major websites by today\u2019s outage below:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021.png\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-27820 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"875\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021.png 864w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021-213x300.png 213w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021-726x1024.png 726w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021-768x1084.png 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021.png 864w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021-213x300.png 213w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021-726x1024.png 726w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/AK-outage-7-22-2021-768x1084.png 768w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></p><div class=\"relpost-thumb-wrapper\"><div class=\"relpost-thumb-container\"><h3>Related posts:</h3><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div style=\"clear: both\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-container\"><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/tarsnap-cloud-backups-for-the-truly-paranoid/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"TarSnap\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/tarsnap-150x150.png) no-repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 150px; height: 150px;\"></div><div class=\"relpost-block-single-text\" style=\"font-family: Arial;  font-size: 12px;  color: #333333;\">Tarsnap: Cloud Backups for the Truly Paranoid</div></div></a><a class=\"relpost-block-single\" href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/running-like-a-swiss-watch-interview-with-andrew-azarov-cto-of-serverastra/\"><div class=\"relpost-custom-block-single\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 215px;\"><div class=\"relpost-block-single-image\" alt=\"ServerAstra Logo\" style=\"background: transparent url(https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/serverastra-150x150.png) no-repeat scroll 0% 0%; width: 150px; hei